Built to Meet Our Clients’ Needs

Lambton Industrial Services Limited (LIST) is a certified and trusted industrial service provider specializing in inspection, fabrication, and construction support across Canada’s major industries — including oil & gas, chemical processing, potash mining, pulp & paper, and power generation.

Our reputation is founded on safety, quality craftsmanship, and technical excellence. With decades of combined field experience, our team ensures every project is delivered safely, efficiently, and to the highest industry standards.

Certifications & Licensing

LIST operates under multiple recognized industry codes and authorizations, fully licensed by the Technical Standards and Safety Authority (TSSA) to perform fabrication, installation, and repair across:

  • Process Piping (ASME B31.3): Fabrication and repair of process systems for industrial facilities.
  • Power Piping (ASME B31.1): Installation and maintenance of high-pressure power systems.
  • Refrigeration Piping (CSA B52): Construction and modification of cooling and refrigeration lines.
  • Boiler & Pressure Vessel (CSA B51): Fabrication and repair-in-kind of boilers, pressure vessels, and associated piping.

These authorizations ensure full compliance with Ontario’s Boilers & Pressure Vessels Regulations (O. Reg. 220/01) and Pressure Piping (O. Reg. 219/01).

Compliance & Quality Assurance

  • ASME Codes: B31.1 (Power Piping), B31.3 (Process Piping), Section VIII (Pressure Vessels)
  • CSA Standards: B51 (Boiler, Pressure Vessel & Piping Code), B52 (Refrigeration Code)
  • TSSA Requirements: Registration, inspection, and documentation for traceability and compliance

Our CSA-Certified Letter of Validation and robust Quality Control Program include detailed ITPs, weld mapping, NDE coordination, hydrotesting, and complete turnover packages — managed by certified quality professionals.

Capabilities

  • Piping fabrication, installation, and modification
  • Boiler and pressure vessel construction and repair
  • Structural steel refurbishment and installation
  • Equipment setting, alignment, and rigging
  • Coating, painting, and surface preparation

We support clients as both prime contractors and subcontractors, offering turnkey solutions for shutdowns, maintenance, and capital projects.

Piping Fabrication

In-shop and field fabrication for carbon, stainless and alloy systems, including spool fabrication, fit-up and installation. Full QA/QC with weld mapping, NDE coordination, pressure tests (hydro/pneumatic) and turnover packages.

  • Spool fabrication to ASME B31.1 / B31.3 with traceable MTRs
  • Field tie-ins, hot taps and small-bore/tubing work
  • Supports, spring cans and specialty items to detail
  • Shop blasting/coating and packaging for transport

Fabrication — Structural Steel

Shop‑built components for platforms, access and protection. We plan fabrication with constructability in mind and align deliveries to your outage or maintenance windows.

Scope We Cover

  • Access platforms (straight and circular), equipment platforms
  • Mono‑rail beams, door lintels, shelf angles
  • Stairways, ladders, catwalks, handrails and guards
  • Stair treads, floor plates and kick plates
  • Machine bases, screens, strainers, debris guards
  • Miscellaneous structural steel and site‑fit adjustments

Execution Approach

Drawings are reviewed against plant standards and field constraints. Material is verified on receipt, welds are inspected to procedure, and finished items are protected for transport. Documentation packs include mill certs and inspection records as requested.

Outcome You Can Expect

Reliable fit‑up, clean finishes and the paperwork your QC team expects—delivered on the date we commit to.

Welding Machine Calibration

Consistent settings lead to consistent welds. Our service verifies and adjusts output to keep equipment within tolerance and documentation ready for audits.

Benefits

  • Better bead appearance and repeatability across shifts
  • Lower rework and consumable waste
  • Confidence during inspections and audits
  • Longer equipment life and fewer call‑outs

Typical Procedure

  • Verify input power and inspect leads, feeders and connections
  • Measure output voltage/current and adjust to spec
  • Set and confirm wire‑feed speed; check shielding gas flow if used
  • Record results and provide a calibration report
